<h2 id="create-an-im-group">Create an IM Group</h2>

<p>Create a IM Group under your account</p>

<blockquote>
<p>Definition</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code>POST https://api.zoom.us/v2/im_groups
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>Example Request</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight shell tab-shell"><code><span class="gp">$ </span>curl https://api.zoom.us/v2/im_groups <span class="se">\</span>
   -d <span class="s1">'{
    "name": "string",
    "type": "string",
    "search_by_domain": "boolean",
    "search_by_account": "boolean",
    "search_by_ma_account": "boolean"
}'</span>
</code></pre>
<blockquote>
<p>Example Response</p>
</blockquote>
<pre class="highlight plaintext"><code>201 Created
</code></pre>
<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Body Arguments</th>
<th>&nbsp;</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>name</td>
<td>Group name, must be unique in one account</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>type</td>
<td>IM Group type<div class="enum"><code class="prettyprint">normal</code> Only members can see the group automatically. Other people can search members in the group<br/><code class="prettyprint">shared</code> All people in the account can see the group and members automatically<br/><code class="prettyprint">restricted</code> Nobody can see the group or search members except the members in the group<br/></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>search_by_domain</td>
<td>Members can search others in the same email domain</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>search_by_account</td>
<td>Members can search others under same account</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>search_by_ma_account</td>
<td>Members can search others under same master account, including all sub accounts</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
